hopobject.body: I'm sorry, he's atorvastatin generic availability date The authors say: "In this prospective cohort study of middle-aged and older women, we observed a statistically significant inverse association between intake of dietary long-chain n-3 Pufas and rheumatoid arthritis. Long-term consistently high intake in 1987 and 1997 of at least 0.21g per day (corresponding to at least one serving per week of fatty fish, such as salmon, or four servings per week of lean fish, for example cod) was associated with a 52% decrease in risk of rheumatoid arthritis. Consistent long-term consumption of fish once or more per week was associated with a 29% decreased risk."
